Durham is a Canadian parish in Restigouche County, New Brunswick.


== Delineation ==
Durham Parish is defined in the Territorial Division Act as being bounded:

East and south by the County lines; west by Colborne Parish, and north by Chaleur Bay including all the islands in front.


== Communities ==
Parish population total does not include incorporated municipalities (in bold or italics).


